    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So let's say you want to add searchForFacetValues to your refinement list: \r\n\r\n```js\r\nrender()\r\n{\r\n  const facetHits = this.props.facetHits.map(facet = > {\r\n    return \r\n    <label>\r\n      <input type=\"checkbox\"\r\n             checked={facet.isRefined}\r\n             onChange={() => {\r\n               this.props.refine(facet.value)\r\n             }}/>\r\n      {facet.value}\r\n    </label>\r\n  }\r\n)\r\n  return (\r\n    <div>\r\n      <input onChange={e => {\r\n        this.props.searchForFacetValues(e.target.value)\r\n      }}\r\n             type=\"search\"/>\r\n      {facetHits}\r\n      {/* markup of the refinement list*/}\r\n    </div>);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is of course not a complete working example, it's just to give you an idea of the usage of the `searchforFacetValues` and how to retrieve the `facetsHits`.\r\n\r\nIMO we should just modify our current connector and widget. As for the widget, displaying the input should be configurable through a prop.  ",
